<p>
  The assessor should provide a conclusion on whether it is clear why any of the
  existing measures have been modified and why the additional existing measures
  are relevant for the descriptor and how they contribute to achieving the
  objectives of MSFD. Background information about the measures can be found in
  &lsquo;measure description&rsquo; (which is an option field) or in the text
  report. The other schema fields mentioned above (&lsquo;Source of
  information&rsquo;) can help gather more details regarding the measure.
</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Use of response options:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      <strong>Yes</strong>: the explanations provided by the MS on the modified
      and additional existing measures are clear and adequate.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      <strong>Partially</strong>: the explanations provided by the MS on the
      modified and additional existing measures are partially clear and adequate
      (e.g. measure description schema field is empty but there is some
      information in the text report), or they are clear and adequate but only
      for some of all the existing measures modified/added.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      <strong>Not clear: </strong>there is some information, but not enough/not
      clear enough to understand how the updates to the existing measures
      contribute to achieve GES;
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      <strong>No: </strong>some existing measures are reported as
      &lsquo;modified since 2015 POM&rsquo; and/or &lsquo;new in 2021
      POM&rsquo;, but there is no explanation as to why (i.e. measures
      description field is empty and there is not additional information in the
      text report).
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      <strong>Not relevant</strong>: No existing measures are reported as
      &lsquo;modified since 2015 POM&rsquo; and/or &lsquo;new in 2021 POM&rsquo;
      and no important policy developments have been missed. If the assessor
      thinks that there should updates related to some policy developments,
      clear explanations as to why should be added. he/she should add a comments
      on what would be expected and then a recommendation at the end (the
      response option remains &lsquo;not relevant&rsquo;).
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<p lang="en-US"><br /></p>
<p><strong>Structure of summary box:</strong></p>
<p>
  Start by stating which response option you have selected and continue
  explaining why. E.g. &lsquo;
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      &lsquo;The MS has not explained how the updates/changes to the existing
      measures from the first cycle contribute to achieving GES&rsquo;; or
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      &lsquo;The MS has clearly explained how the updates/changes to the
      existing measures from the first cycle contribute to achieving GES&rsquo;
      or
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      The MS has only partially explained how the updates/changes to the
      existing measures from the first cycle contribute to achieving GES&rsquo;.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      &lsquo;It is not clear whether the MS has explained how the
      updates/changes to the existing measures from the first cycle contribute
      to achieving GES&rsquo;.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      &lsquo;Not relevant because the MS has not reported any change to existing
      measures&rsquo;.
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<p><br /></p>
<p>The assessor must:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      <u><strong>List in bullet points format</strong></u> the existing measures
      that are modified and the additional existing measures (new category 1
      measures), if any (i.e. measures that were adopted for the purpose of
      other policies
      <u>after the Programme of Measures 2016-2021 had been established</u>).
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      Always mention the code and the title of the measures and provide short
      summary of the measure.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      Differentiate between existing measures from WFD and existing measures
      from other policies.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      Indicate whether the MS specified the different categories of measures
      1a/1b
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      Specify whether the link between the modified /additional existing
      measures and the other policies is clear and relevant.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p lang="fr-BE">Are relevant KTM reported?</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<p lang="fr-BE">
  Are all relevant policies/legislation covered? Is there anything that the MS
  has missed?
</p>
